ed finisher at the 2022 Austrian Grand Prix, which takes place over 71 laps of the 4.318-kilometre Red Bull Ring in Spielberg on Sunday, July 10.\n\nThe market will resolve to “Verstappen” if Max Verstappen finishes ahead of Charles Leclerc, and “Leclerc” if Charles Leclerc finishes ahead of Max Verstappen. \n\nNote:\n- If Max Verstappen finishes the race but Charles Leclerc does not, or does not compete at all, the market will resolve to “Verstappen”. \n- If Charles Leclerc finishes the race but Max Verstappen does not, or does not compete at all, the market will resolve to “Leclerc”. \n- If neither Charles Leclerc nor Max Verstappen finish the race before July 17 (11:59 PM ET), then the market will resolve to 50-50. \n- If for any reason the 2022 Austrian Grand Prix is rescheduled to a different time and date on or before July 17, 2022, the same market conditions will apply. If the race is rescheduled to a time and date after July 17, 2022, this market will resolve to 50-50.","outcomes":"[\"Verstappen\", \"Leclerc\"]","outcomePrices":"[\"0.000000689240582043482038042890082149935\", \"0.9999993107594179565179619571099179\"]","volume":"2090.881955","active":true,"marketType":"normal","closed":true,"marketMakerAddress":"0xB64f1962171fe42ac22C85174255a52F11687873","updatedBy":15,"createdAt":"2022-07-08T17:11:59.224Z","updatedAt":"2023-01-31T17:36:44.543Z","closedTime":"2022-07-10 18:46:01+00","wideFormat":true,"new":false,"sentDiscord":false,"featured":false,"submitted_by":"0x400567bc06000e36db66f725f16d08f4C579D1Fe","twitterCardLocation":"https://polymarket-upload.s3.us-east-2.amazonaws.com/formula-1-who-will-finish-ahead-at-the-2022-austrian-grand-prix-max-verstappen-or-charles-leclerc.png?1657478414592","twitterCardLastRefreshed":"1657478414593","twitterCardLastValidated":"1657479438.3679469","archived":false,"resolvedBy":"0xCB1822859cEF82Cd2Eb4E6276C7916e692995130","restricted":true,"marketGroup":494,"groupItemTitle":"Will Verstappen or Leclerc finish ahead?","gro